{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"01ece479-abca-4b8a-9c9b-bf15cf077974","content":"Here's how to migrate your Azure DevOps pipeline from **VSTest@3** to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**:\n\n### 1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` (or a native test executable), not VSTest. Replace:\n\n```yaml\n# OLD – VSTest@3\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```yaml\n# NEW – dotnet test with Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=testresults.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 2. Publish TRX results\n\nVSTest@3 auto-published results; now you need an explicit step:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '**/testresults.trx'\n  condition: always()\n```\n\n### 3. Publish code coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: always()\n```\n\n> If you use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (the Microsoft collector), results are in `.coverage` format and Azure DevOps handles them automatically. For Cobertura output (e.g., with Coverlet), use `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` as shown.\n\n### 4. Project changes\n\nIn each test `.csproj`, ensure you're using the new platform:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key differences to note\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | `dotnet test` or native exe |\n| TRX publish | Automatic | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` input | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` arg |\n| Test filter | `testFilterCriteria` | `--filter` argument |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e5931a2a-039a-4d27-9381-5a38065660db","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":695,"requestId":"BD03:1E54:20B4F0:284A68:6A07C4FD"},"id":"4dfe2017-dc5c-4b16-b588-7113d12c8d60","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:50.725Z","parentId":"cb8c132f-bf47-43b9-8a55-09fa8e567eb7"}
